Alan Shearer says he does not hold much hope for former club Newcastle United and fears a ‘long, hard season’ lies ahead.

The Magpies are without a win this term and reside in the bottom three going into Saturday’s home game with Leicester City.

Manager Alan Pardew has seen off intense speculation surrounding his future - at least in the short-term - and retains the support of owner Mike Ashley.

