But Shearer has not been impressed by performances on the pitch. Indeed, his hometown team have collected just 20 points from a possible 78 since the turn of the year.

He told the Chronicle: ‘It has been poor since January this year,’ said the club’s record goalscorer, who netted 206 times during 10 years on Tyneside.

‘I’m exactly the same as the fans at the minute - I’m one of them.

‘I pay for my ticket and I’m the same. I am entitled to my opinion.

